From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Date: Mon, 22 Jul 2019 20:47:07 +0200
Subject: x86/apic: Invoke perf_events_lapic_init() after enabling APIC
Patch-mainline: v5.4-rc1
Git-commit: 39c89dff9c366ad98d2e5598db41ff9b1bdb9e88
References: bsc#1162702

If the APIC is soft disabled then unmasking an LVT entry does not work and
the write is ignored. perf_events_lapic_init() tries to do so.

Move the invocation after the point where the APIC has been enabled.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Acked-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/20190722105218.962517234@linutronix.de
Acked-by: Daniel Wagner <dwagner@suse.de>
---
 arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c |    5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kernel/apic/apic.c
@@ -1559,7 +1559,6 @@ static void setup_local_APIC(void)
 	int logical_apicid, ldr_apicid;
 #endif
 
-
 	if (disable_apic) {
 		disable_ioapic_support();
 		return;
@@ -1574,8 +1573,6 @@ static void setup_local_APIC(void)
 		apic_write(APIC_ESR, 0);
 	}
 #endif
-	perf_events_lapic_init();
-
 	/*
 	 * Double-check whether this APIC is really registered.
 	 * This is meaningless in clustered apic mode, so we skip it.
@@ -1656,6 +1653,8 @@ static void setup_local_APIC(void)
 	value |= SPURIOUS_APIC_VECTOR;
 	apic_write(APIC_SPIV, value);
 
+	perf_events_lapic_init();
+
 	/*
 	 * Set up LVT0, LVT1:
 	 *
